{ [%csl Rf3][%cal Rg1f3] }
1. Nf3 c5 { Not everytime we will play d4! We will play the sneaky move a3. } { [%csl Ba3][%cal Ba2a3] } 2. a3!? $140 { This looks like a very weird move at first glance, but we have an idea to play b4! } { [%csl Rb4][%cal Rb2b4] } 2... Nc6 { We do it anyways! } { [%csl Yb4][%cal Yb2b4] } 3. b4! { We will gambit a pawn for activity. Declining the gambit with e6 doesn't work because we just take and play d4. e5 also doesn't work due to b5. } 3... cxb4 { Recapture. } { [%csl Gb4][%cal Ga3b4] } 4. axb4 Nxb4 { Develop the bishop to a3. } { [%csl Ya3][%cal Yc1a3] } 5. Ba3 Nc6 { Push the pawn up to e4! } { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4] } 6. e4! { We gain central space! } { [%csl Rf5,Rd5][%cal Re4d5,Re4f5] } 6... e6 { Take the bishop on f8. } { [%csl Yf8][%cal Ya3f8] } 7. Bxf8 Kxf8 { Control the center with d4. } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] } 8. d4 { Engine says this is equal, but white has high chances of winning! } { [%csl Rd5][%cal Rd4d5] } *


