{ [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] }
1. Nf3 d5 { Go for the kingside fianchetto. } { [%cal Bg2g3] } 2. g3 Nf6 { Develop the bishop. } { [%csl Bg2][%cal Bf1g2] } 3. Bg2 Bf5 { Push pawn up to c4. } { [%csl Bc4][%cal Bc2c4] } 4. c4 e6 { Develop the queen to b3. } { [%csl Rb7][%cal Rb3b7,Bd1b3] } 5. Qb3 Nc6 { Castle the king. } 6. O-O (6. Qxb7 { This is a bit risky as they can play Nb4 and threaten a fork on c2. } { [%csl Rc2][%cal Rb4c2,Rc2a1,Rc2e1,Bc6b4] }) 6... a6 { Develop the knight. } { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 7. Nc3 Be7 { Push pawn to d3. } { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bd2d3] } 8. d3 h6 { Play Nh4. } { [%csl Rf5][%cal Gf3h4,Rh4f5] } 9. Nh4 Bh7 { Take the pawn. } { [%csl Bd5][%cal Bc4d5] } 10. cxd5 exd5 { Take it with the knight. } { [%csl Rd5][%cal Rc3d5] } 11. Nxd5 Nxd5 { Take with the bishop. } { [%csl Yd5][%cal Yg2d5] } 12. Bxd5 Bxh4 { Take the pawn on f7. } { [%csl Rf7][%cal Rd5f7] } 13. Bxf7+ Kf8 { Take the bishop. } { [%csl Bh4][%cal Bg3h4] } 14. gxh4 Qxh4 { Very natural move, but you play Be3 and you win. } { [%csl Be3][%cal Bc1e3] } 15. Be3 $18 { [%csl Rf8][%cal Re3c5,Rc5f8] } *


