{ [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] }
1. Nf3 Nf6 { [%csl Bg3][%cal Bg2g3] } 2. g3 g6 { [%csl Rg2][%cal Rf1g2] } 3. Bg2 Bg7 { [%csl Gg1][%cal Ge1g1] } 4. O-O O-O { [%csl Yd3][%cal Yd2d3] } 5. d3 d6 { [%csl Rc4][%cal Rc2c4] } 6. c4 { You can also play c4 in the King's Indian Attack. } 6... e5 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 7. Nc3 Nc6 { [%csl Rb1][%cal Ra1b1] } 8. Rb1 { You want to play the move b4 and gain queenside space. } { [%csl Rb4][%cal Rb2b4] } 8... a5 { Prepare to fianchetto the second bishop. } { [%csl Bb3][%cal Bb2b3] } 9. b3 h6 { [%csl Bb2][%cal Bc1b2] } 10. Bb2 Be6 { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4] } 11. e4 { Clamp on d5 has been created... } { [%csl Rd5][%cal Rc4d5,Re4d5] } 11... Qd7 { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bd1d2] } 12. Qd2 { We have finished development. } { [%csl Rg2,Rf3,Rd2,Rc3,Rb2] } 12... Bh3 { [%csl Be1][%cal Bb1e1] } 13. Rbe1 Bxg2 14. Kxg2 Nh5 { [%csl Bd5][%cal Bc3d5] } 15. Nd5 $16 { We now play chess. Your main pawn break is d4 and once you achieve that, black will have issues in their position due to lack of space. } { [%csl Rd4][%cal Rd3d4] } *


