{ [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] }
1. Nf3 Nf6 { [%csl Bg3][%cal Bg2g3] } 2. g3 d5 { [%csl Rg2][%cal Rf1g2] } 3. Bg2 c6 { [%csl Yg1][%cal Ye1g1] } 4. O-O Bf5 { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bd2d3] } 5. d3 e6 { Nfd2... a pretty interesting move with the plan to play e4. } { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bf3d2] } 6. Nfd2!? { Prepares e4. } { [%csl Be4][%cal Gd3e4,Gd2e4,Gg2e4,Be2e4] } (6. Nbd2 { Other knight... }) 6... h6 { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4] } 7. e4 Bh7 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bb1c3] } 8. Nc3 { We will have a strong kingside attack later on. } 8... Be7 { Push f4! Attack on the kingside! } 9. f4 O-O { [%csl Bh1][%cal Bg1h1] } 10. Kh1 { Prophylactic move to get out of the weakened diagonal... } { [%csl Rg1][%cal Ra7g1] } 10... a5 { [%csl Bg4][%cal Bg3g4] } 11. g4 a4 { [%csl Bh4][%cal Bh2h4] } 12. h4 { Full attack mode... } { [%csl Be4,Bf4,Bg4,Bh4] } 12... a3 { [%csl Bg5][%cal Bg4g5] } 13. g5 { We don't care about their attack on the queenside. Their kingside is currently on fire! } 13... Nfd7 { [%csl Bb1][%cal Ba1b1] } 14. Rb1 { Defending a bit... } 14... hxg5 { [%csl Bg5][%cal Bh4g5] } 15. hxg5 $16 { Pressure along the h-file is going to be dangerous for black... } { [%csl Bh3,Rh8,Rh7][%cal Bf1f3,Bf3h3,Rd1h5,Rh5h8,Bh3h5] } *


