{ [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] }
1. Nf3 e6 { [%csl Bg3][%cal Bg2g3] } 2. g3 d5 { [%csl Rg2][%cal Rf1g2] } 3. Bg2 Nf6 { [%csl Rd3][%cal Rd2d3] } 4. d3 c5 { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 5. O-O Nc6 { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bb1d2] } 6. Nbd2 Be7 { [%csl Ye4][%cal Ye2e4] } 7. e4 O-O { [%csl Re1][%cal Rf1e1] } 8. Re1 b5 { Push or take? } { [%csl Re5,Gd5][%cal Re4e5,Ge4d5] } 9. exd5 $140 { The idea of this is to play d4 next move! } { [%csl Rd4][%cal Rd3d4] } (9. e5 { We have covered this already in the previous chapter... }) 9... exd5 { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd3d4] } 10. d4 c4 { [%csl Be5][%cal Bf3e5] } 11. Ne5! { Outpost knight on e5... } 11... Bb7 { [%csl Bc6][%cal Be5c6] } 12. Nxc6 Bxc6 { [%csl Ra4][%cal Ra2a4] } 13. a4 a6 { [%csl Yb5][%cal Ya4b5] } 14. axb5 axb5 { [%csl Ba8][%cal Ba1a8] } 15. Rxa8 Bxa8 { ...Maybe you thought they could take with the queen?? The bishop on e7 hangs because of our perfectly placed rook on e1! } { [%csl Bf1][%cal Bd2f1] } 16. Nf1 { [%csl Be5,Rf5,Ge2,Yh4][%cal Bc1f4,Bf4e5,Re3f5,Gd1e2,Rf1e3,Yh2h4] } *


