{ [%csl Bf3][%cal Bg1f3] }
1. Nf3 c5 { [%csl Bc4][%cal Bc2c4] } 2. c4 { Transposition into English Opening... } 2... Nf6 { [%csl Bg3][%cal Bg2g3] } 3. g3 Nc6 { [%csl Bg2][%cal Bf1g2] } 4. Bg2 g6 { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 5. O-O Bg7 { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] } 6. d4 cxd4 { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gf3d4] } 7. Nxd4 O-O { [%csl Yc3][%cal Yb1c3] } 8. Nc3 Qa5 { This is their best move... } { [%csl Be3][%cal Be2e3] } 9. e3 d6 { Don't grab the free candy! It isn't a trap, but you fall behind in development. Just develop the bishop to d2. } { [%csl Bd2][%cal Bc1d2] } 10. Bd2 { X-ray on the queen... hmm... } { [%csl Ra5,Rc3][%cal Rd2a5] } 10... Bd7 { They ignore it, push pawn to b3... } 11. b3 { [%csl Rb3,Rc4][%cal Rb3c4,Ra2b3] } 11... Rfc8 { [%csl Bh3][%cal Bh2h3] } 12. h3 { Just waiting to strike at the right moment. } 12... Qd8 { [%csl Bc1][%cal Ba1c1] } 13. Rc1 a6 { [%csl Be2][%cal Bd1e2] } 14. Qe2 Rab8 { [%csl Gd1][%cal Gf1d1] } 15. Rfd1 Nxd4 { Most popular but dubious because we get our center. } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Be3d4] } 16. exd4 b5 { [%csl Bc5][%cal Bc4c5] } 17. c5 { Sac a pawn? Hmm... } 17... dxc5 { [%csl Rf4][%cal Rd2f4] } 18. Bf4 cxd4 { [%csl Bb8][%cal Bf4b8] } 19. Bxb8 $18 { We win the exchange and we are winning! } *


