{ You know what to play!!! }
1. Nf3 Nf6 { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bd2d4] } 2. d4 g6 { Instead of playing Bf4, you could also play Nbd2. } { [%csl Yd2][%cal Yb1d2] } 3. Nbd2 { While you are learning the Reti Opening, you are also learning a bunch of different openings because they usually transpose into each other. } 3... Bg7 { [%csl Ye4][%cal Ye2e4] } 4. e4 { Central space has been generated... } { [%csl Rc5,Re5,Rf5,Rd5][%cal Rd4e5,Rd4c5,Re4d5,Re4f5] } 4... d6 { [%csl Bd3][%cal Bf1d3] } 5. Bd3 O-O { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 6. O-O Nc6 { [%csl Bc3][%cal Bc2c3] } 7. c3 e5 8. Re1 Qe7 { [%csl Bf1][%cal Bd2f1] } 9. Nf1 { A pretty solid position for white with a comfortable game ahead... } { [%csl Rg3,Re3,Yh5,Ge2,Bb4][%cal Rf1g3,Rf1e3,Yh2h4,Yh4h5,Gd1e2,Ba2a3,Ba3b4] } *


